        @Deprecated
DBID get(int i)
        Deprecated. Preferably use a DBIDArrayIter or a DBIDVar instead of materializing expensive DBID objects.
        Get the i'th entry (starting at 0) If possible, use an DBIDArrayIter via iter() instead, or an DBIDVar via assignVar(int, de.lmu.ifi.dbs.elki.database.ids.DBIDVar)
        Parameters:
        i - Index
        Returns:
        DBID of i'th entry.

      • binarySearch

        int binarySearch(DBIDRef key)
        Search for the position of the given key, assuming that the data set is sorted. For keys not found, -(1+insertion position) is returned, as for Java Collections.binarySearch(java.util.List<? extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>, T)
        Parameters:
        key - Key to search for
        Returns:
        Offset of key
